    "plan_content": "## Implementation Plan: `ollama rename`\n\nHere's the complete plan across **4 files** (no test files modified):\n\n---\n\n### 1. `api/types.go` — Add `RenameRequest`\nAfter the existing `CopyRequest` struct (line 765), add:\n```go\ntype RenameRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `api/client.go` — Add `Rename()` client method\nAfter `Copy()` (line 387), following the exact same pattern:\n```go\nfunc (c *Client) Rename(ctx context.Context, req *RenameRequest) error {\n    if err := c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil); err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `server/routes.go` — `RenameHandler` + route registration\n\n**Handler** (inserted after `CopyHandler` at line 1483):\n1. Bind JSON request body (400 on bad body)\n2. `model.ParseName(r.Source)` + `IsValid()` check (400 on invalid)\n3. `getExistingName(src)` for case-canonicalization\n4. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → **404** if `os.ErrNotExist`\n5. `model.ParseName(r.Destination)` + `IsValid()` check (400 on invalid)\n6. `getExistingName(dst)` for case-canonicalization\n7. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` — if **no error** → **409 Conflict**\n8. `CopyModel(src, dst)` (500 on error)\n9. `m.Remove()` + `m.RemoveLayers()` on source (500 on error)\n10. Return **200 OK**\n\n**Route** (after `r.POST(\"/api/copy\", ...)` at line 1698):\n```go\nr.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)\n```\nNo new imports needed — all required packages already present.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `cmd/cmd.go` — CLI handler + cobra command\n\n**`RenameHandler` func** (after `CopyHandler` at line 1350):\n```go\nfunc RenameHandler(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n    client, _ := api.ClientFromEnvironment()\n    req := api.RenameRequest{Source: args[0], Destination: args[1]}\n    if err := client.Rename(cmd.Context(), &req); err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    fmt.Printf(\"renamed '%s' to '%s'\\n\", args[0], args[1])\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n**`renameCmd`** (after `copyCmd` at line 2263):\n```go\nrenameCmd := &cobra.Command{\n    Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\", Short: \"Rename a model\",\n    Args: cobra.ExactArgs(2), PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat, RunE: RenameHandler,\n}\n```\n\nAdd `renameCmd` to both the **env-docs loop** and **`rootCmd.AddCommand(...)`**, alongside `copyCmd`.\n\n---\n\n### Error table\n\n| Condition | HTTP |\n|---|---|\n| Missing/bad body | 400 |\n| Invalid name | 400 |\n| Source not found | **404** |\n| Destination exists | **409** |\n| Storage failure | 500 |\n| Success | 200 (empty body) |",
